				 BJP jab at Left
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, Oct. 9: The BJP today told the Left parties that running a coalition was not in the Congresss DNA, fanning the soaring tension between the ruling partners.																								Needling the Left two days after Sonia Gandhis remarks on nuclear power took matters to a flashpoint, the BJP asked the UPA ally to recall how many times it had been victimised by the arrogant Congress.																								One is surprised as to how parties of the Left failed to note that running a coalition government is not in the DNA of Congress, the BJP said in a statement . 																								The Congress has a dominant arrogant character fuelled by the conviction that it has a sole monopoly to decide as to what is in Indias interest, the statement said.
